renden Instanz, sondern auch zu einer Logik der emotiv und voluntativ gesteuerten Bewußtseinsakte, die sie als eine Erlebnisform von "Werten" erkennt. Die paradoxen Entwicklungsbedingungen der Moderne werden durch Aufklärung dieser komplexen Sachverhalte durchsichtig.  aThe study examines the thoroughgoing re-evaluation of the foundations of human knowledge that set in around the year 1830. Of crucial significance in structural terms is the relation between ideas on the soul and natural science. In the context of the 'atomization' of knowledge following the collapse of Romantic nature philosophy, Herbart, Lotze and Fechner developed strategies for a 'concentration' of all branches of knowledge in a unified model not only accelerating the modernization process but also fulfilling a compensatory function. Their debates on the origins and processing of knowledge represents a highly influential redefinition of the epistemological function and cultural relevance of the aesthetic.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aAesthetics, Germany19th century. 0aImmanence (Philosophy)zGermanyxHistoryy19th century. 0aPsychology and philosophyzGermanyxHistoryy19th century. 4aFechner, Gustav Theodor. 4aHerbart, Johann Friedrich. 4aLotze, Hermann (Philosoph). 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / German.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Literary and Cultural Studies - 1990 - 1999z9783110637830oZDB-23-GLC0 cprintz978348435063240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311091667640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110916676423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110916676/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-GLCc1990d1999